[location trigger] The players enter the tavern, the atmosphere warm and inviting.
[npc trigger] Joe the tavern keeper looks up and greets the newcomers with a nod.
[player]: Joe, you seem like someone who knows what's happening in this town.
[joe_tavernier]: Well, I've seen more ships come and go than most folks have seen in their lifetimes. So, yeah, I do pick up a few tales here and there. What brings you to the Rusty Anchor tonight?
[player]: I'm an adventurer looking for work. Are there any problems around here that need solving?
[joe_tavernier]: Ah, well, there's always something going on in this town. You've got the lighthouse ghosts, goblins raiding the farms, and some folks think someone's stealing grain from the harbor warehouse. What kind of job are you looking for exactly?
[player]: A tavern keeper usually hears about all sorts of troubles. Anything going on that needs attention?
[joe_tavernier]: Tavern life is a mix of drinks and dirt. The lighthouse has been giving folks the creeps, the goblins are causing trouble up north, and some grain's been disappearing from the docks. Not to mention, we've got a mysterious new face around these parts. What can I get you involved in?
[player]: I'm skilled at handling dangerous situations. If there's any trouble in the area, I can help.
[joe_tavernier]: Goblin raids and lighthouse disturbances sound like your cup of tea. Captain Hilda Ironforge is recruiting mercenaries for a mission to clear out some bandits from the woods. Might be worth checking out if you're looking for action. And don't forget, we've got a new stranger on the docks—might want to keep an eye on him too.
[player]: Have you heard of any issues with thieves, bandits, or creatures causing problems?
[joe_tavernier]: Thieves and bandits are a dime a dozen in these parts, but I haven't seen anything out of the ordinary myself. The goblins up north are more of a hassle, and the lighthouse has been giving folks the creeps at night. Keep an eye on that new chap on the docks—there's something fishy about him.
[player]: I'd be happy to take care of any pest problems or investigate suspicious activities for you.
[joe_tavernier]: Alright, well, if you're keen on it, I can use a pair of hands around here. The grain theft at the harbor warehouse is bothering everyone, and maybe you could check out those goblin raids in the northern farms. If you get your hands dirty and find anything, let me know. And don't forget to keep an eye on that new guy—there's always trouble when strangers show up.